The paper deals with a caching network, which involves storing and retrieving data from a database. This falls under the category of information theory (cs.IT) and networked systems (cs.NI). The paper also proposes a novel caching scheme, which involves optimizing the placement of data in the cache, which falls under the category of data structures (cs.DS) and systems and control (cs.SY). Finally, the paper uses mathematical techniques to derive the rate-memory tradeoff, which falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG).
